The Houston Astros have announced the implementation of a program designed to

give Enron employees exclusive mini-plan seating in the Dugout Boxes and

Terrace Deck at Enron Field.


&Our relationship with Enron is one of the greatest partnerships in

professional sports, and this is yet another way for us to say thanks.8

Astros Vice President of Ticket Services John Sorrentino said.


The exclusive 27-game offer, which expires March 14, includes seating in

Field Box Sections 132 and 133 and Terrace Deck Sections 305, 306 and 307.

Cost per seat is $675 on the Field Box level and $324 for the Terrace Deck

level seats. Enron employees are the first to be offered these packages in

the Field and Terrace Deck levels and those who respond will be eligible for

limited playoff options and receive a red mesh adjustable batting practice

cap, while supplies last. Seating is non-renewable and subject to

availability.


Enron employees interested in taking advantage of the program should call

Astros Ticket Services at (713) 259-8500 or email Astros Sales Manager Matt

Rogers at rogers@astros.com. When calling or writing, please identify

yourself as an Enron employee.


Find information about the three mini-plans at www.astros.com and hope to see

you at Enron Field.


